21:53.604 --> 21:55.105
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:55.105 --> 21:56.982
<i>‐ Once the glue dries</i>
<i>and I take the clamps off,</i>

21:56.982 --> 21:58.192
<i>I head over to the grinder</i>

21:58.192 --> 21:59.985
and I begin to rough‐out
the handle,

21:59.985 --> 22:01.278
give it a nice shape

22:01.278 --> 22:02.988
<i>so I can begin to make it</i>
<i>more comfortable</i>

22:02.988 --> 22:04.865
<i>in the hand.</i>

22:04.865 --> 22:06.492
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:06.492 --> 22:07.576
<i>‐ Bryce seems to like</i>
<i>that angle grinder.</i>

22:07.576 --> 22:08.994
‐ Yeah, he does.

22:08.994 --> 22:10.371
I mean, there's a lot of guys

22:10.371 --> 22:12.164
that do most of their shaping
on an angle grinder.

22:12.164 --> 22:13.332
It's what they have;

22:13.332 --> 22:14.458
that's what they get used to.

22:14.458 --> 22:15.543
‐ I'm enjoying it.

22:15.543 --> 22:17.211
It reminds me
of being back home.

22:17.211 --> 22:19.338
‐ Well, Bryce is going back
to his comfort level,

22:19.338 --> 22:22.007
but can he clean up nicely
using the angle grinder?

22:22.007 --> 22:23.175
‐ I don't know.

22:23.175 --> 22:25.135
‐ It's all about
the skill level.

22:25.135 --> 22:26.720
‐ Five minutes, bladesmiths.

22:26.720 --> 22:28.347
Just five minutes remaining.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.849
<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

22:29.849 --> 22:31.517
‐ So I've gotten the edge
of my blade,

22:31.517 --> 22:33.644
<i>and I'm trying to shave</i>
<i>my hair a little bit,</i>

22:33.644 --> 22:37.857
and I go for one more swipe,
