‐ Nah, some other guy
did it.

22:54.331 --> 22:55.875
[laughing]
‐ It will skin.

22:55.875 --> 22:58.127
‐ It will skin!

22:58.127 --> 23:01.338
<i>[heavy metal bass riff]</i>

23:01.338 --> 23:02.506
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:02.506 --> 23:05.175
Five! Four! Three!

23:05.175 --> 23:07.219
Two! One!

23:07.219 --> 23:08.929
Bladesmiths,
stop what you're doing,

23:08.929 --> 23:10.222
drop your tools.

23:10.222 --> 23:13.684
This second round
of competition is over!

23:13.684 --> 23:15.269
‐ Good [bleep], man.
Good [bleep].

23:15.269 --> 23:17.396
<i>‐ Going into testing,</i>
<i>kind of nervous</i>

23:17.396 --> 23:19.607
<i>to see how the judges test</i>
<i>my blade</i>

23:19.607 --> 23:21.066
<i>right in front of me.</i>

23:21.066 --> 23:23.694
But no going back now.

23:23.694 --> 23:26.071
‐ Bladesmiths, welcome
to our strength test,

23:26.071 --> 23:27.406
the bamboo chop.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.533
Now, this tough,
springy material's

23:29.533 --> 23:31.577
not only gonna test
the edge of your blades,

23:31.577 --> 23:32.912
but it's also gonna test

23:32.912 --> 23:34.371
the overall construction
of your knife.

23:34.371 --> 23:35.748
This is gonna be
a lot of fun,

23:35.748 --> 23:36.749
at least for me.

23:36.749 --> 23:37.917
And Colton, you're up first.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.084
How are you feeling?
‐ Good.

23:39.084 --> 23:40.544
‐ Good? I feel good too.

23:40.544 --> 23:41.670
Let's go.

23:41.670 --> 23:43.088
<i>[intense music]</i>

23:43.088 --> 23:46.926
<i>‐ I know J. hits really,</i>
<i>really hard,</i>

23:46.926 --> 23:48.427
<i>so I'm a little nervous</i>

