25:37.578 --> 25:39.038
Good job, Craig.
‐ Thank you.

25:39.038 --> 25:40.080
‐ The edge is perfect.

25:40.080 --> 25:41.623
Nothing wrong with it.

25:41.623 --> 25:43.375
I like the look of it.
I like the feel of it.

25:43.375 --> 25:45.586
Overall, a really good job.

25:45.586 --> 25:47.421
‐ Thank you.

25:47.421 --> 25:49.465
<i>[quiet, tense music]</i>

25:49.465 --> 25:50.799
‐ All right, bladesmiths.

25:50.799 --> 25:52.426
This is our sharpness test,

25:52.426 --> 25:54.928
the rope bridge slice.

25:54.928 --> 25:56.388
Now, unlike the strength test,

25:56.388 --> 25:58.223
this is all about what the edge
of your weapon

25:58.223 --> 25:59.558
will do to the rope.

25:59.558 --> 26:01.393
Colton, you're up first.
Are you ready for this?

26:01.393 --> 26:02.728
‐ Yep.
‐ Let's do this.

26:02.728 --> 26:07.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:07.900 --> 26:10.903
<i>[aggressive drumming]</i>

26:10.903 --> 26:17.868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:19.286 --> 26:20.579
‐ Yeah. Good cuttin'.

26:20.579 --> 26:21.747
Good cut.

26:21.747 --> 26:23.082
‐ All right, Colton.

26:23.082 --> 26:24.917
Let's talk about your chopper,
here.

26:24.917 --> 26:28.087
Nice and clean lines,
shiny,

26:28.087 --> 26:29.838
and more importantly,
one and done

26:29.838 --> 26:30.964
for every slice.

26:30.964 --> 26:33.592
It will cut.

26:33.592 --> 26:34.802
All right, Bryce,
your turn.

26:34.802 --> 26:36.011
Are you ready?
‐ I'm ready.

26:36.011 --> 26:37.137
‐ Let's do this.

26:37.137 --> 26:40.182
<i>[intense, percussive music]</i>

26:40.182 --> 26:44.561
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:44.561 --> 26:47.606
<i>[aggressive rock music]</i>

26:47.606 --> 26:49.942
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:49.942 --> 26:51.610
‐ Good job.
‐ Good job.

26:51.610 --> 26:52.778
‐ Good job.

