that rope.

27:27.604 --> 27:30.649
<i>[energetic heavy metal]</i>

27:30.649 --> 27:32.484
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:32.484 --> 27:35.153
[wood clatters on floor]

27:35.153 --> 27:36.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:36.530 --> 27:39.491
‐ [relieved grunting]

27:39.491 --> 27:40.826
‐ All right, Craig.

27:40.826 --> 27:42.494
What is your knife like?

27:42.494 --> 27:44.413
It's got a nice curved edge,

27:44.413 --> 27:45.789
to when you're swinging it,

27:45.789 --> 27:49.334
I can feel the curve
and it slices nicely.

27:49.334 --> 27:51.587
And most of all, sir,
it will cut.

27:51.587 --> 27:53.881
‐ Ah, thank you very much.

27:53.881 --> 27:56.008
<i>[steady, tense music]</i>

27:56.008 --> 27:57.593
‐ Bladesmiths,
in these deliberations

27:57.593 --> 27:59.386
the judges have to consider

27:59.386 --> 28:01.680
not just how your blades
performed in the tests,

28:01.680 --> 28:03.849
but also feel, fit, and finish.

28:03.849 --> 28:05.517
They've made
their final decision.

28:05.517 --> 28:08.687
It's time for one of you smiths
to leave The Forge.

28:08.687 --> 28:11.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:11.023 --> 28:14.776
