we're sending you home.

28:30.709 --> 28:32.044
‐ I understand.

28:32.044 --> 28:34.630
‐ Bryce, please surrender
your blade.

28:34.630 --> 28:35.881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:35.881 --> 28:37.758
<i>‐ I do 100% agree</i>
<i>with the judges.</i>

28:37.758 --> 28:40.052
<i>I respect their opinions</i>
<i>on my blade.</i>

28:40.052 --> 28:41.887
This was a great competition.

28:41.887 --> 28:43.764
<i>I'm not disappointed</i>
<i>in myself.</i>

28:43.764 --> 28:46.058
My blade held up
to all the tests.

28:46.058 --> 28:48.060
<i>I came here to prove</i>
<i>that I can compete</i>

28:48.060 --> 28:49.728
<i>with other bladesmiths</i>
<i>out there.</i>

28:49.728 --> 28:52.397
I definitely believe
I proved it.

28:52.397 --> 28:54.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:54.232 --> 28:56.026
‐ Bladesmiths, congratulations.

28:56.026 --> 28:57.569
You've made it
to the final round

28:57.569 --> 28:58.612
of this competition.

28:58.612 --> 29:00.072
When you showed up here,

29:00.072 --> 29:02.699
we had you make Monosteel blades
with blue handles

29:02.699 --> 29:04.576
to honor Big Blu.

29:04.576 --> 29:06.745
Now we're sending you back
to your home forges

29:06.745 --> 29:09.665
to recreate an iconic weapon
from history.

29:09.665 --> 29:12.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:12.042 --> 29:15.420
It's a rock‐throwing crossbow,
gentlemen.

29:15.420 --> 29:16.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:16.588 --> 29:17.839
<i>The rock‐throwing crossbow,</i>

29:17.839 --> 29:19.257
<i>also known as a stone bow,</i>

29:19.257 --> 29:20.968
<i>was developed</i>
<i>in the 14th century</i>

29:20.968 --> 29:23.261
<i>but gained popularity</i>
<i>with outdoorsmen</i>

29:23.261 --> 29:25.097
<i>during the 17th century.</i>

29:25.097 --> 29:27.432
<i>Instead of sharpened quarrels</i>
<i>or bolt projectiles,</i>

29:27.432 --> 29:30.769
<i>the stone bow was loaded</i>
<i>with small stones or pellets.</i>

29:30.769 --> 29:33.021
<i>The stone bow harnessed</i>
<i>less launching power</i>

29:33.021 --> 29:35.607
<i>than war bows, as they were</i>
<i>specifically designed</i>

29:35.607 --> 29:37.401
<i>for hunting game silently.</i>

29:37.401 --> 29:39.528
<i>Its small stone or pellet</i>
<i>projectiles</i>

29:39.528 --> 29:40.821
<i>were readily available,</i>

29:40.821 --> 29:42.280
<i>and left its target</i>
<i>untarnished or destroyed</i>

29:42.280 --> 29:44.282
<i>by punctures</i>
<i>from the steel‐tipped arrows,</i>

29:44.282 --> 29:46.702
<i>preserving pelts</i>
<i>for luxury clothing.</i>

29:46.702 --> 29:49.496
<i>This made it a popular weapon</i>
<i>among experienced hunters,</i>

29:49.496 --> 29:50.956
<i>and a perfect choice</i>

29:50.956 --> 29:53.542
<i>as a young hunter's</i>
<i>first crossbow.</i>

29:53.542 --> 29:55.544
You're both talented guys.

29:55.544 --> 29:58.130
Don't be afraid to put
a little flavor on it.

29:58.130 --> 30:01.174
Just make sure that it falls
within the following parameters.

30:01.174 --> 30:03.343
Your rock‐throwing crossbow
must include

30:03.343 --> 30:05.971
a prod, a pocketed string,

30:05.971 --> 30:07.806
a trigger‐release mechanism,

30:07.806 --> 30:09.599
a stock and pommel.

30:09.599 --> 30:11.309
You'll have four days
at your home forges

30:11.309 --> 30:12.978
in which to complete
this challenge.

30:12.978 --> 30:14.354
At the end of those four days,

30:14.354 --> 30:16.148
you'll return and present
your crossbows

30:16.148 --> 30:17.858
to our panel of expert judges,

30:17.858 --> 30:20.318
and after they've tested them
thoroughly,

30:20.318 --> 30:22.362
they'll declare one of you
the "Forged in Fire" champion

30:22.362 --> 30:25.657
who walks out of here
with a check for 10 grand.

30:25.657 --> 30:26.825
Good luck, bladesmiths.

30:26.825 --> 30:28.243
We'll see you in four days.

30:28.243 --> 30:30.287
‐ Okay.

30:30.287 --> 30:34.082
<i>[hard rock guitar riff]</i>

30:34.082 --> 30:35.333
[train whistle]

30:35.333 --> 30:36.668
<i>It's day one.</i>

30:36.668 --> 30:37.961
<i>I'm back</i>
<i>in the bubbling metropolis</i>

30:37.961 --> 30:39.504
<i>of Franklin, Illinois,</i>

30:39.504 --> 30:42.049
and I'm ready to get started
on this stone bow.

30:42.049 --> 30:44.801
<i>So this build,</i>
<i>it's a technical build, right?</i>

30:44.801 --> 30:45.927
<i>You're not just building</i>
<i>a blade,</i>

30:45.927 --> 30:47.220
<i>you're building a machine,</i>

