31:25.383 --> 31:28.053
That's a pretty sound.

31:28.053 --> 31:29.221
Right now, I'm feeling
pretty good.

31:29.221 --> 31:30.847
I know I got a lot of work
ahead of me.

31:30.847 --> 31:32.599
I'm ready.
Let's go into day two.

31:32.599 --> 31:35.143
<i>[hard rock guitar riff]</i>

31:35.143 --> 31:38.063
<i>‐ So it's day one back here</i>
<i>in Ceresco, Nebraska,</i>

31:38.063 --> 31:41.441
and I'm gonna be making
a rock‐throwing crossbow.

31:41.441 --> 31:43.193
<i>I started out making crossbows</i>

31:43.193 --> 31:44.402
<i>when I was really young,</i>

31:44.402 --> 31:45.570
so the knowledge of the physics

31:45.570 --> 31:46.905
and, like, how they work

31:46.905 --> 31:49.407
is definitely gonna help
a lot in this challenge.

31:49.407 --> 31:50.575
For all the metal parts,

31:50.575 --> 31:52.577
I'm gonna be using mild steel,

31:52.577 --> 31:54.788
<i>and for the bow, I'm gonna</i>
<i>be using 5160,</i>

31:54.788 --> 31:57.415
